title: The Deathstone
description: A radioactive meteor crashes on Earth and V.E.N.O.M. steals it by disguising Switchblade as a U.F.O.

title: The Star Chariot
description: V.E.N.O.M. are on the hunt to find the missing part of the Emerald Arrowhead, which will lead to an alien spacecraft, the Star Chariot.

title: The Book of Power
description: V.E.N.O.M. steals the Book of Power, which is the key to the Lost City of Mong Paco and its giant jewel-covered idol.

title: Highway to Terror
description: M.A.S.K are on a mission to recover hugely radioactive plutonium that V.E.N.O.M. have stolen from an army vehicle.

title: Video VENOM
description: V.E.N.O.M. learn to hypnotize people through their televisions in order to help in their plans to incinerate an oil base in Texas.

title: Dinosaur Boy
description: V.E.N.O.M. kidnaps a young lizard creature known as a "dinosauroid".

title: The Ultimate Weapon
description: V.E.N.O.M. use a "cyclonic disruptor" to interfere with the operating systems of M.A.S.K.'s vehichles.

title: The Roteks
description: V.E.N.O.M. steal a colony of metal-eating insects developed for warfare.

title: The Oz Effect
description: Sly Rax disguises himself an aboriginal priest. V.E.N.O.M. has a machine that causes a giant vortex which they use to "kidnap" the village people.

title: Death from the Sky
description: V.E.N.O.M. terrorize military aircraft with a submarine that is equipped with an anti gravity force-field and a tractor ray.

title: The Magma Mole
description: V.E.N.O.M. has a drilling vehicle called The Magma Mole that they are using to burrow beneath Tokyo to create devastating floods.

title: Demolition Duel to the Death
description: 'Clutch' Hawkes, driving Wildcat, is competing in the Memphis Demolition Derby against Vanessa 'Snake' Warfield in Manta and 'Mad Dog' Shepard with Stinger. When Boris 'The Czar' Bushkin makes a memorable entrance driving Bulldog, Vanessa tries to recruit the Russian into VENOM and set a trap for Clutch with Lester 'The Lizard' Sludge on Iguana.

title: Where Eagles Dare
description: Matt Trakker in Goliath 1 races the Mayhem brothers in Buzzard to secure an African Trade Route for the Peaceful Nations Alliance. But while Matt goes it alone, the Mayhems have Mad-dog, Bird-man and The Lizard to back them up.

title: Homeward Bound
description: Ali Bombay returns to his home town of Kandukar in India for some rest only to find VENOM agents Lester 'The Lizard' Sludge and Nash 'Goon' Gorey terrorizing the village. They are rounding up workers to mine the minerals of a meteorite in a cave. Sludge dares Bombay to a race claiming that VENOM will leave the area if he loses.

title: The Battle of the Giants
description: Goliath and Volcano compete against Buzzard and Vampire in the Australia outback's "Battle of the Giants" to win the late Proffesor McDonald's secret metal formula. Trakker 'no-plan' involves using no tricks at all, which is the exact opposite of what Mayhem is expecting.

title: Race Against Time
description: Brad 'Chopper' Turner enters the Mediteranian Grand Prix at Gibraltar to transport a valuable life saving plant across the finish line. Vanessa Warfield and Mad Dog Sheppard are doing anything and everything to stop him. While Sly 'Wrecker' Rax and Dusty 'Cowboy' Hayes man the sidelines.

title: Challenge of the Masters
description: Ali 'Lightning' Bombay competes in the Masters Challenge Race with Ace 'Falcon' Riker as backup. A microfilm stolen from Peaceful Nations Allegiance is being smuggled inside the Masters trophy. This means Vanessa and Bird-Man Malloy will do anything to win. Mayhem (disguised as a peanut seller) and Mad-Dog are waiting on the sidelines but so are a couple of under cover M.A.S.K. agents.

title: For One Shining Moment
description: Maximus Mayhem tries to convince his brother Myles to go legitimate and reconcile with his former partner in science, Matt Trakker. But while the former enemies compete in a friendly race in Chicago, Clutch Hawkes is lured into a trap.

title: High Noon
description: The M.A.S.K. race team takes a vacation at the Wichita Kansas car races and air show and when a couple of VENOM agents show up, they appear to only be their to race as well. But when Ace 'Falcon' Riker's flying stunt show is sabotaged by Buzzard's drone, it becomes clear there's more at stake than just rest and relaxation.

title: The Battle for Baja
description: Mexican president Vega lets M.A.S.K. enter the Baja race, but only if his son Raoul can drive Goliath. Wildcat and Bulldog's rematch is interrupted as VENOM, represented by Buzzard, Vampire and Iguana, are out to kidnap the President's son. Luckily Clutch and the Czar get some help from The Chief and Lightning.

title: Cliff Hanger
description: The rivalry between Vanessa Warfield and Brad Turner heats up at the Mesa Verde Memorial Road Race. Nevada 'The Chief' Rushmore has asked Turner, Calhoun Burns and Ali Bombay to represent his tribe. Vanessa and fellow VENOM agents Bruno Sheppard and Floyd Malloy are also competing for an extinct tribe that mysteriously vanished. Meanwhile Lester Sludge has gotten his hands on a container of dangerous seeds that can can cause insanity when added to water.
